# Test: `ze config validate` gates the traffic-control subtree via the CLI's
# build-tagged default helper.
# VALIDATES: spec-fw-9 AC-4 -- the offline CLI runs the backend feature gate
#            on traffic-control and falls back to trafficDefaultBackend()
#            when the user omits the `backend` leaf. On Linux that helper
#            returns "tc" so validation succeeds; on non-Linux it returns
#            "" and the walker's empty-backend guard fires -- mirroring
#            the daemon's reload-time diagnostic. This .ci exercises the
#            Linux branch end-to-end.
# PREVENTS: regression where the `traffic-control` row falls out of the
#           gated-components table and the CLI silently accepts configs
#           the daemon would later reject at commit time, OR where the
#           trafficDefaultBackend() helper drifts from the runtime
#           default (caught in addition by default_backend_traffic_test.go).

option=skip-os:value=darwin
stdin=config:terminator=EOF_CONF
traffic-control {
}
EOF_CONF

cmd=foreground:seq=1:exec=ze config validate -:stdin=config
expect=exit:code=0
expect=stdout:contains=configuration valid
